
Todays Soft Skill Tip:

Day 28 – Confidence Framing: Sound Certain, Even When Unsure

Everyone faces moments of doubt 0 but professionals know how to frame their answers confidently even when they don’t know everything.

Confidence framing is about focusing on what you do know instead of apologizing for what you don’t.

People trust calm honesty over nervous perfection.

Task:
When you’re unsure in conversation or an interview, say:

“I haven’t explored that fully yet, but here’s how I’d approach it.”
Practice this line aloud today - it instantly shifts your tone from fearful to solution-minded.
